paramName - The name of the parameter - maps to a fact is the ArchE Core.
ownerSlot - The integer owner (parent) slot of the fact.
valueSlot - The string value slot of the fact.
dataType - The parameter value can be any one of string, boolean or float. This is a constant that lets us know which data type value is to be asserted.

modifyResponsibility

public void modifyResponsibility(jess.Rete engineArchE,
                                 ResponsibilityVO voRInitial,
                                 java.lang.String descriptionSlot)
Modifies a responsibility fact in the ArchE Core. Even though the findFactByFact method exposed by the Rete class is faster than findFactByID (as documented in the API documentation) we have changed the implementation to use the latter because the former implies complete knowledge of the fact structures in the Arche Core. Using the latter allows for modifiability over performance - becasuse the fact structures can change without "finding the fact in the core bridge" ever becoming a problem.

Parameters:
engineArchE - The centrally located Rete object using which the fact is retracted.
voRInitial - The Responsibility Value Object which is to be modified.
descriptionSlot - The modified string description slot of the fact.

modifyResponsiblityParameter

public void modifyResponsiblityParameter(jess.Rete engineArchE,
                                         ParameterVO voParamInitial,
                                         int ownerSlotI,
                                         int ownerSlotM,
                                         java.lang.String valueSlotM,
                                         int dataType)
Modifies a "parameter of a responsibility" fact in the ArchE Core. Even though the findFactByFact method exposed by the Rete class is faster than findFactByID (as documented in the API documentation) we have changed the implementation to use the latter because the former implies complete knowledge of the fact structures in the Arche Core. Using the latter allows for modifiability over performance - becasuse the fact structures can change without "finding the fact in the core bridge" ever becoming a problem.

Parameters:
engineArchE - The centrally located Rete object using which the fact is asserted.
voParamInitial - the original Parameter Value Object
ownerSlotI - The initial integer owner (parent) slot of the fact.
ownerSlotM - The modified integer owner (parent) slot of the fact.
valueSlotM - The modified string value slot of the fact. If the user has left the cell corresponding ot this value blank, pass 0 (zero) for this parameter
dataType - The parameter value can be any one of string, boolean or float. This is a constant that lets us know which data type value is to be asserted.

Retracts the following - the Responsibility Fact - the Parameters of the responsibility - the relationships of the responsibility - the parameters of the responsibility relationshipsa responsibility and its associated parameters and relationships from the ArchE Core.

Parameters:
engineArchE - The centrally located Rete object using which the fact is retracted.
applyToSlotD - the fact Id of the Responsbility that is to be deleted.
